9.4: Working from Home

**The URACIL cluster can be accessed by home by installing some freeware.**

****Step 1: VPN****

**In order to gain access to the cluster and shared directory, you must log into the University of Lethbridge secure server. Your Bridge username and password are used to verify your identity.**

<http://www.uleth.ca/information-technology/services/remote-access-vpn>

****Step 2: WinSCP****

**In the place of the SFTP window used on campus, we use the WinSCP program. Similar to SFTP, the left side corresponds to the Windows machine and the right side to the Unix machine. The login window asks for the Host name, your username and your URACIL password. This information can be saved.**

<https://winscp.net/eng/download.php>

![](data:image/png;base64,)

****Step 3: PuTTy****

**In the place of SSH Secure Shell, you can use PuTTy. WinSCP automatically comes with a button to open PuTTy; however, the PuTTy.exe file must be saved to your program files folder (Program File(X86) for a 64-bit system) in a folder called PuTTY. Once you download the .exe file, simply make a new folder in this location and move the executable there. When you open PuTTY, the window will initially ask for the host name. Once the Unix terminal opens it will ask for your username and password. Note that the cursor will not move when you enter your password.**

<http://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~sgtatham/putty/latest.html>
